== Credits ==

This product uses the source code derived from,
    GNOME Shell
GNOME Shell is licensed under the terms of the GPL-2.0-or-later.
The original software is available from,
    https://wiki.gnome.org/Projects/GnomeShell

Like the other GNOME On-Screen Keyboard extensions, this product uses
the basic On-Screen Keyboard extension mechanism developed from,
    https://github.com/schuhumi/gnome-shell-extension-improve-osk

Indicator, a keyboard button shown in the top bar, is based on the work at,
    https://github.com/Bradan/Gnome-On-Screen-Keyboard-Button
